    "body": "A few thoughts:\r\nProbably we can't manipulate smart contracts because we need to keep OpenZeppelin implementation in order to work correctly with OpenSea, and other vendors. We need to keep standards.\r\nWe can optimize smart contract compilation, however then we need to check: deployment cost and all other operations cost (airdrop, burning), because optimisation has impact on them.\r\nA sensible approach is to make such optimization in the end when we have all functionalities implemented. Then we can compare costs.\r\nDeployment on Optimism is not so expensive.",
